10
00:02:08,896 --> 00:02:12,316
Well, a decade ago,
I founded a small nonprofit

11
00:02:12,399 --> 00:02:14,985
and I built it into
a major global player.

12
00:02:15,069 --> 00:02:18,781
I shepherded a number of bills
through Congress on its behalf.

13
00:02:18,864 --> 00:02:22,701
And over the last year, I've dedicated
myself to sexual assault reform,

14
00:02:22,785 --> 00:02:25,037
and have made meaningful strides.

15
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:28,040
Now, while this
may not qualify as statecraft,

16
00:02:28,123 --> 00:02:30,376
it does illustrate my effectiveness,

17
00:02:30,459 --> 00:02:33,587
the same effectiveness I plan
on bringing to the United Nations.

18
00:02:33,671 --> 00:02:37,174
Thank you, Mrs. Underwood.
I yield the remainder of my time.

19
00:02:38,676 --> 00:02:42,221
Uh, Mrs. Wallace of North Dakota,
you have eight minutes.

20
00:02:42,304 --> 00:02:44,265
Thank you, Mr. Chairman.

21
00:02:44,348 --> 00:02:47,559
Mrs. Underwood,
allow me to get specific.

22
00:02:47,643 --> 00:02:51,105
What is your take
on UN Resolution 9214,

23
00:02:51,188 --> 00:02:54,441
the imposition of sanctions
on the Congo for the--

24
00:02:54,525 --> 00:02:57,361
The illegal mining and smuggling
of mineral resources.

25
00:02:57,444 --> 00:03:00,572
Yes. The United States voted
against this resolution.

26
00:03:00,656 --> 00:03:04,326
The DRC is already wracked
with economic hardship,

27
00:03:04,410 --> 00:03:06,120
compounded by an unstable government.

28
00:03:06,203 --> 00:03:10,290
It ranks 192 out of 194
in GDP per capita.

29
00:03:10,374 --> 00:03:12,918
I think we need
to encourage foreign investment

30
00:03:13,002 --> 00:03:15,129
and develop new forms of economic growth

31
00:03:15,212 --> 00:03:18,757
rather than make one of the world's
poorest countries even poorer.

32
00:03:18,841 --> 00:03:20,843
From a national security perspective,

33
00:03:20,926 --> 00:03:24,596
the United States maintains a strong
interest in the success of the DRC.

34
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:26,849
- We want a stable nation...
- They're here.

35
00:03:26,932 --> 00:03:29,601
...that can help us
in combating the spread

36
00:03:29,685 --> 00:03:32,813
of Islamic radicalism
throughout the continent.

37
00:03:32,896 --> 00:03:35,858
And in order to achieve that,
we need to work as its ally,

38
00:03:35,941 --> 00:03:37,484
not its disciplinarian.

39
00:03:40,738 --> 00:03:41,864
Good morning.

40
00:03:41,947 --> 00:03:42,865
Mr. President.

41
00:03:45,784 --> 00:03:48,454
Jackie. Terry.

42
00:03:48,537 --> 00:03:50,039
Shall we?

43
00:03:50,122 --> 00:03:53,167
Now you all have the, uh... overview.
But what we have here today

44
00:03:53,250 --> 00:03:55,669
- is the comprehensive breakdown--
- Sir, before we begin--

45
00:03:55,753 --> 00:03:58,464
Look, Bob, I know you have some
serious doubts about this program.

46
00:03:58,547 --> 00:04:01,342
But just let me flesh it out first,
and then I promise

47
00:04:01,425 --> 00:04:03,886
we can address any questions
that you might have.

48
00:04:03,969 --> 00:04:06,305
- Uh, Mr. President--
- Ten million jobs.

49
00:04:06,388 --> 00:04:09,141
Can we all agree that that's
a good thing for this country?

50
00:04:09,224 --> 00:04:10,893
Universal employment.

51
00:04:10,976 --> 00:04:13,854
It's the key for our keeping
the White House in 2016.

52
00:04:13,937 --> 00:04:16,982
It's the only chance we have
of winning back majorities in Congress.

53
00:04:17,066 --> 00:04:19,026
Now, the election's
only 18 months away.

54
00:04:19,109 --> 00:04:22,154
We need to do something bold,
something decisive.

55
00:04:22,237 --> 00:04:24,114
We need to redefine our party.

56
00:04:24,198 --> 00:04:26,408
Actually, that's what
we wanted to discuss.

57
00:04:26,492 --> 00:04:28,285
You're right, we do need
to redefine the party.

58
00:04:28,369 --> 00:04:29,828
We need to do it
with a fresh face.

59
00:04:29,912 --> 00:04:32,331
2016. We don't want you to run.

60
00:04:32,414 --> 00:04:34,917
You weren't even elected
to the office in the first place.

61
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:37,628
The pardons hurt you.
Approvals are low.

62
00:04:37,711 --> 00:04:39,004
We're not casting blame, sir.

63
00:04:39,088 --> 00:04:42,132
We just believe that this
is best for the party.

64
00:04:51,683 --> 00:04:54,561
I suspected this was coming,
but months from now.

65
00:04:54,645 --> 00:04:57,481
I was hoping by then I'd have something
to show for my efforts,

66
00:04:57,564 --> 00:05:00,234
that I could preempt their doubts
with progress.

67
00:05:00,317 --> 00:05:03,028
They're nervous.
They're being impulsive.

68
00:05:03,112 --> 00:05:06,031
It's a bit early
to be deciding something like this.

69
00:05:06,115 --> 00:05:08,617
Shouldn't we revisit this
when we're closer to the primaries?

70
00:05:08,700 --> 00:05:10,160
What do you think, Terry?

71
00:05:10,244 --> 00:05:12,579
Like you said, sir, we only
have 18 months until the general.

72
00:05:12,663 --> 00:05:13,956
Less than half of that to Iowa.

73
00:05:14,039 --> 00:05:15,833
We would want to settle
on a candidate soon.

74
00:05:15,916 --> 00:05:17,501
Someone who the whole party
can get behind

75
00:05:17,584 --> 00:05:19,420
like the Republicans
are getting behind Mendoza.

76
00:05:19,503 --> 00:05:20,671
And who would that be?

77
00:05:20,754 --> 00:05:22,464
We haven't had
a discussion on that yet.

78
00:05:22,548 --> 00:05:24,591
We came to you first, out of respect.

79
00:05:24,675 --> 00:05:27,845
- Well, there must be a shortlist.
- No, not yet.

80
00:05:27,928 --> 00:05:30,264
It'll be a process
to find the right person.

81
00:05:30,347 --> 00:05:32,933
And we were hoping that
you would be a part of that process.

82
00:05:33,016 --> 00:05:35,561
Obviously, this is a request,
Mr. President.

83
00:05:35,644 --> 00:05:37,062
It's your decision.

84
00:05:37,146 --> 00:05:40,399
But if you do run, sir,
you won't have our support.

85
00:05:41,692 --> 00:05:43,318
Jackie?

86
00:05:45,487 --> 00:05:47,698
I stand by the rest of the leadership.

87
00:05:51,034 --> 00:05:53,328
Well, this is certainly a lot
to think about.

88
00:05:53,412 --> 00:05:56,331
Let's table our discussion
on America Works for another time,

89
00:05:56,415 --> 00:05:58,250
but thank you all
for being so forthright.

90
00:05:58,333 --> 00:06:00,586
I'll get back to you
on this issue a little later on.

91
00:06:00,669 --> 00:06:02,629
Would you like us
to stick around for a while?

92
00:06:02,713 --> 00:06:04,923
